menu "WellD Configuration"

    config WELLD_SLEEP_DURATION_SEC
        int "Deep sleep duration (seconds)"
        default 300
        range 30 3600
        help
            Baseline sleep duration between wakeups. When adaptive sleep is
            enabled, this is the "normal-rate-of-change" window; the actual
            sleep duration is scaled up when the level is stable and down
            when it's changing fast. Note: the fast-rate target is
            default/4 (integer division); at the minimum value of 30 s this
            equals 7 s, which the WELLD_SLEEP_MIN_SEC floor immediately
            overrides — very short base values make the fast-rate band
            unreachable.

    config WELLD_ADAPTIVE_SLEEP_ENABLED
        bool "Adaptive sleep duration"
        default y
        help
            Adjust sleep duration based on the level rate-of-change observed
            between the last two wakeups. Stable wells get longer sleeps
            (saving battery); fast-changing wells get shorter sleeps
            (catching transients). Disable to use WELLD_SLEEP_DURATION_SEC
            verbatim.

    config WELLD_SLEEP_MIN_SEC
        int "Adaptive sleep — minimum (seconds)"
        default 60
        range 30 3600
        depends on WELLD_ADAPTIVE_SLEEP_ENABLED
        help
            Lower bound on adaptive sleep. The device will never sleep less
            than this even when the level is changing rapidly.

    config WELLD_SLEEP_MAX_SEC
        int "Adaptive sleep — maximum (seconds)"
        default 1800
        range 60 7200
        depends on WELLD_ADAPTIVE_SLEEP_ENABLED
        help
            Upper bound on adaptive sleep. The device will never sleep
            longer than this, even when the level is perfectly stable.

endmenu

menu "Rev 2 Hardware I/O"

config WELLD_CHARGER_CE_GPIO
    int "TP4056 charger CE interlock GPIO"
    range 0 21
    default 4
    help
        Drives Q1 gate (BSS123). HIGH disables USB charging (TP4056 CE LOW).
        Assert when solar charging is active to prevent dual-charger conflict.

config WELLD_SOLAR_DETECT_GPIO
    int "Solar charging detect GPIO (CN3791 CHRG)"
    range 0 21
    default 6
    help
        Input. HIGH when the CN3791 MPPT charger is actively charging.
        Used to gate the TP4056 interlock.

config WELLD_MAX17048_ALRT_GPIO
    int "MAX17048 ALRT input GPIO"
    range 0 21
    default 14
    help
        Active-low open-drain alert from MAX17048 fuel gauge. External pull-up
        R27 (4.7 kOhm to 3.3 V) is required on the PCB. Can be configured as
        a deep-sleep wakeup source for low-battery alerting.

endmenu
